Position Summary: 
Reporting to the Chief Financial Officer, the Chief Information Officer will be responsible for all aspects of Information Technology in the Company including all software applications, computer hardware, cyber security, data bases, and connectivity of the various locations of the Company. The CIO will be a business partner with the management team with the responsibility to effectively support the ongoing IT needs of the business as well as creating and implementing a strategic vision for the implementation of a fully integrated ERP platform across the Company. The ability to effectively work with the leadership team and the Board of Directors in understanding both the current and long term needs of the business as well as bringing innovative new ideas and technologies is critical to the success of the role. 
 Essential Job Functions Include: 
Maintain the effective deployment and support for all software applications used by the Company including version upgrades, network infrastructure, and security. 
Provide proactive partnership with the executive leadership team to understand the IT needs and requirements of the ongoing operations of the Company as well as existing projects which need the support of IT
 Analyze the technology currently in use to ensure efficiency, accuracy and security.
 Stay current with the latest developments and capabilities of IT including artificial intelligence and data analytics
 Lead a companywide effort to create a road map and vision for a fully integrated ERP platform for the Company to support future growth of the Company. This effort includes obtaining alignment of all key stakeholders as well as obtaining board approval for the project.
 Oversee projects and assignments within the IS department. 
Communicate goals, projects, and timelines of the company to the department; plan ways to execute those goals within the department; and conduct performance evaluations that are timely and constructive. 
Identify new IS developments and technologies; anticipate resulting organizational modifications. 
Ensure that IS and network infrastructure adequately support the companyâ€™s computing, data processing, reporting and communications needs. 
Develop and manage the IS budget.
 Ensure compliance with government regulations that apply to systems operations. 
Manage outsider vendors and contractors providing IS services. 
Maintain security of company information and information systems. 
Perform other related duties as assigned.
